article.headline: The Citadel 68, Chattanooga 60
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Zach Urbanus scored 24 points, hitting seven 3-pointers, and Cameron Wells had a double-double to lead The Citadel to a 68-60 win over Chattanooga on Saturday night. Wells, who made 8 of 11 free throws, finished with 11 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists for the Bulldogs (12-12, 6-8 Southern Conference), who ended a three-game losing streak. Austin Dahn had 11 points. The Citadel, which never trailed in the second half, took a 49-40 lead on Dahn's 3-pointer with 8:49 to play. The Mocs (13-12, 5-7) cut the Bulldogs' margin to one with 4:52 left on two free throws by Chris Early, who had 10 points. But The Citadel withstood Chattanooga's attempted rally, pushing its lead to 61-53 on Bo Holston's three-point play with 2:46 left to help the Bulldogs pull away. Ty Patterson led the Mocs with 19 points and six rebounds. Ridge McKeither had 13 points and 18 rebounds.
